The paper discusses the use of recurrent neural networks in sequence learning tasks such as language modelling, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of sparse activations and boosting, which are common techniques in neural network optimization (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper applies the model to language modelling tasks, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper uses the MNIST dataset, which is commonly used in computer vision tasks (cs.CV).
